-- Poland to Dismiss KGHM CEO Wirth, Puls Biznesu Reports
-- B y   M o n i k a   R o z l a l
-- 2011-12-20T06:14:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-20/poland-to-dismiss-kghm-ceo-wirth-puls-biznesu-reports.html
Poland’s Treasury Ministry plans to
dismiss  Herbert Wirth  as the chief executive officer of  KGHM
Polska Miedz SA (KGH) , the state-controlled copper producer,  Puls
Biznesu  reported, without citing anyone or giving more detail.  Wirth was to be dismissed last week, according to the
newspaper, but Treasury Ministry did not want to affect the
company’s share price after the details of new mining tax and
KGHM’s takeover plans were revealed.  Calls placed to KGHM and the Treasury Ministry out of
office hours went unanswered.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Monika Rozlal in Warsaw at 
 mrozlal@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  